        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 27 at 10:17PM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 1017 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Sonora, moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Sonora, Ozona, The Intersection Of Us 190 And Highway 163, Us-
277 Near The Sutton-
Schleicher County Line, The Intersection Of Ranch Road 2596 And Ranch
Road 864, I-10 Near The Crockett-
Sutton County Line, and The Intersection Of I-10 And Ranch Road 1989.

This includes Interstate 10 between Mile Markers 359 and 412.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 100 AM CDT for
west central Texas.</instruction>
